%S A190291 1,3,16,124,1262,15898,238572,4152172,82179608,1821967872,44713134528,
%T A190291 1202987996172,35201532741032,1112838371787424,37791992028679864
%N A190291 Number of intervals in the weak (Bruhat) order of the symmetric group S_n that are distributive lattices.
%C A190291 The intervals [u,v] in the weak order that are distributive lattices are characterized by Stembridge. They are the intervals such that u^{-1}.v is fully commutative, i.e., avoids the pattern 321.
%H A190291 Carlo Corti, <a href="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.21309701">Extending OEIS A190291 via Linear Extensions of Inversion Posets</a>, Zenodo archive, 2026.
%H A190291 J. R. Stembridge, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1023/A:1022452717148">On the Fully Commutative Elements of Coxeter Groups</a>, Journal of Algebraic Combinatorics, 5 (1996), 353-385.
%F A190291 a(n) = Sum_{w in S_n, w avoids 321} e(P(w)), where P(w) is the poset on {1..n} generated by the relations i <_{P(w)} j whenever i < j and w^(-1)(i) > w^(-1)(j), and e(P) denotes the number of linear extensions of P. - _Carlo Corti_, Jul 11 2026
%e A190291 For n=3 there are six 1-element intervals, six 2-element intervals, and four intervals that are 3-element chains, for a total of 16.
%Y A190291 Cf. A007767.
%K A190291 nonn,more,changed
